comment._content: Douglas AD-5 / A-1E Skyraider 132437. Marked MARINES on rear fuselage. Tail code CZ of organisation only referred (via internet) as “HQSQDN-17” Modex code 8 on engine cowl. Light Gull Gray fuselage side very heavily stained with exhaust fumes. Code info courtesy of ‘Skyhawk Association’: a4skyhawk.org/2e/marine-tail-codes.htm Fleet Marine and Marine Support Units Headquarters HQSQDN-17 CZ Color profile of A-1E 132437 with a US Navy training squadron VA-122 marked incorrectly as Modex 076: wp.scn.ru/en/ww3/a/593/3/4#90 (click on picture alongside following text to view profile) AD-5 (A-1E) Unit: VA-122, US Navy Serial: 076/NJ (BuNo.132437) NAS Lemoore, circa 1968. Color picture of actual A-1E 132437 with US Navy training squadron VA-122: www.cloud9photography.us/Military-Aviation-10/Douglas-A-1... Douglas A-1E Skyraider 132437. VA-122, Modex 276. Code NJ. NAS Lemoore 1 June 1968; by Clay Jansson There is reference that A-1E 132437 was accepted into desert storage at the then MASDC near Tucson Arizona on 5 March 1969. It was declared excess on 8 January 1970. Recorded as; US Navy. VA-122 NJ-076 www.amarcexperience.com/AMARCDB.asp?SessionId=563305803&a... Fate as yet unknown.
